<self-uri xlink:href="http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_arttext&amp;pid=S0101-33002018000200335&amp;lng=en&amp;nrm=iso"></self-uri><self-uri xlink:href="http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_abstract&amp;pid=S0101-33002018000200335&amp;lng=en&amp;nrm=iso"></self-uri><self-uri xlink:href="http://www.scielo.br/scielo.php?script=sci_pdf&amp;pid=S0101-33002018000200335&amp;lng=en&amp;nrm=iso"></self-uri><abstract abstract-type="short" xml:lang="pt"><p><![CDATA[RESUMO Uma suposta convergência com o significado hegemônico dos temas da identidade nacional e da cultura brasileira nos anos 1920-1940 tem sido mobilizada para explicar a participação de Mário de Andrade no Estado Novo. Demonstramos, ao contrário, o sentido dissonante e crítico de suas ideias, materializadas nas políticas públicas de democratização da cultura que formulou nos anos 1930, e as tensões que imprimem a esse contexto intelectual e político.]]></p></abstract>
<abstract abstract-type="short" xml:lang="en"><p><![CDATA[ABSTRACT Mário de Andrade&#8217;s ideas are usually seen as similar to the hegemonic meaning taken on by the themes of national identity and Brazilian culture in the 1920s-1940s, and this has been ultimately used to explain his participation in the Estado Novo. On the contrary, the article demonstrates both the dissonant and critical meaning of his ideas, which shaped the public policies for culture democratization he formulated in the 1930s, and the tensions they impinge on this intellectual and political context.]]></p></abstract>
